Wash and dry produce. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounce} in half lengthwise,
then cut into 1/2-inch-thick half-moons. Trim and discard root end from
@baby lettuce{1}; separate leaves. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Place @butter{2%tablespoon} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}. Tightly cover with
#plastic wrap{} and microwave until butter has melted, ~{30-60%seconds}. Stir in
@Frank's hot sauce{3}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; dice into 1/2-inch pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Add chicken, carrots, and @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}; season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked
through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Add Buffalo sauce and cook, stirring, ~{30%seconds}
more. Remove from heat.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @coleslaw mix{4%ounce} and
@blue cheese dressing{1.5%ounce}. Season with @salt{} to taste.

Divide lettuce leaves between plates; fill with Buffalo chicken. Top with tangy
blue cheese coleslaw. Serve with lemon wedges on the side.